comments.description: Given a browser, this creates a snapshot of the content and returns a canvas with the resulting snapshot of the content at the thumbnail size. It has to do this through a two step process: 1) Render the content at the window size to a canvas that is 2x the thumbnail size 2) Downscale the canvas from (1) down to the thumbnail size This is because the thumbnail size is too small to render at directly, causing pages to believe the browser is a small resolution. Also, at that resolution, graphical artifacts / text become very jagged. It's actually better to the eye to have small blurry text than sharp jagged pixels to represent text.
